{"title_page": "Anthony Bright", "text_new": "{{Infobox NFL player\n|image= \n|position=[[Wide receiver]]\n|birth_date={{Birth date and age|1977|3|28|mf=y}}\n|birth_place=[[Gainesville, Florida]]\n|death_date=\n|height_ft = 6\n|height_in = 1\n|weight_lbs = 176\n|high_school = [[Bradford High School (Florida)|Starke (FL) Bradford]]\n|college=[[Valencia Community College|Valencia CC]]\n|undraftedyear=1999\n|teams=\n* [[Houston Marshals]] (1999)\n* [[Jacksonville Tomcats]] ({{af2 Year|2000}}\u2013{{af2 Year|2002}})\n* [[Carolina Panthers]] ({{NFL Year|2002}})\n* [[Houston Texans]] ({{NFL Year|2003}})*\n* [[Scottish Claymores]] (2003)\n* [[Orlando Predators]] ({{AFL Year|2004}})\n* [[Houston Texans]] ({{NFL Year|2004}})*\n* [[Orlando Predators]] ({{AFL Year|2005}})*\n* [[Las Vegas Gladiators]] ({{AFL Year|2005}})*\n* [[Grand Rapids Rampage]] ({{AFL Year|2005}})*\n* [[Philadelphia Soul]] ({{AFL Year|2006}})\n* [[Calgary Stampeders]] ({{CFL Year|2006}})\n|statlabel1=Games Played\n|statvalue1=1\n|aflstatlabel1=Receptions\n|aflstatvalue1=16\n|aflstatlabel2=Receiving yards\n|aflstatvalue2=241\n|aflstatlabel3=Receiving TDs\n|aflstatvalue3=2\n|aflstatlabel4=Returns\n|aflstatvalue4=19\n|aflstatlabel5=Return yards\n|aflstatvalue5=273\n|nfl=2504768\n|pfr=B/BrigAn20\n|afl=4363\n}}\n'''Anthony Leonard Bright''' (born March 28, 1977) is a former [[Canadian football|Canadian]] and [[American football]] [[wide receiver]].  He played for the [[Jacksonville Tomcats]] of the [[af2]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://jacksonville.com/tu-online/stories/081401/spo_6941736.html |title=Arena grads face long odds in NFL |author=Teneshia L. Wright |date=August 14, 2001 |publisher=Jacksonville.com |work=www.jacksonville.com |accessdate=February 11, 2014}}</ref> the [[Carolina Panthers]] of the [[National Football League|NFL]] and the [[Calgary Stampeders]] of the [[Canadian Football League|CFL]].  Bright played [[college basketball]] at [[Valencia Community College]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\